---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MedicalDisclaimer from '../components/MedicalDisclaimer.astro';

const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="About CompareWeightMeds | Our Mission & Team"
  description="Learn about CompareWeightMeds: independent GLP-1 telehealth reviews, transparent pricing comparisons, and our commitment to helping you find safe, affordable weight loss medications."
>
  <style>
    .hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #059669 100%);
      color: white;
      padding: 80px 24px 60px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    
    .hero p {
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      opacity: 0.95;
      max-width: 700px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 60px 24px 80px;
    }
    
    .content h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 48px 0 16px;
    }
    
    .content h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    
    .content h3 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 32px 0 12px;
    }
    
    .content p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text-sec);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    
    .content ul {
      margin: 20px 0;
      padding-left: 24px;
    }
    
    .content li {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text-sec);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    
    .mission-box {
      background: var(--accent-light);
      border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 32px;
      border-radius: var(--r);
      margin: 32px 0;
    }
    
    .mission-box h3 {
      color: var(--accent-dark);
      margin: 0 0 16px 0;
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
    
    .mission-box p {
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    
    .values-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
      gap: 24px;
      margin: 32px 0;
    }
    
    .value-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1.5px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--r);
      padding: 24px;
    }
    
    .value-icon {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    
    .value-card h4 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }
    
    .value-card p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      margin: 0;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>About CompareWeightMeds</h1>
    <p>Independent, transparent reviews of GLP-1 telehealth providers to help you make informed decisions about weight loss medications</p>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <MedicalDisclaimer />
    
    <h2>Who We Are</h2>
    <p>CompareWeightMeds is an independent comparison platform dedicated to helping patients navigate the growing landscape of GLP-1 telehealth providers. We review and score providers based on transparent criteria, providing unbiased information to help you find safe, affordable weight loss medications.</p>
    
    <div class="mission-box">
      <h3>Our Mission</h3>
      <p>To empower patients with transparent, comprehensive information about GLP-1 telehealth options, making weight loss medications more accessible and affordable for everyone.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Why We Built CompareWeightMeds</h2>
    <p>The rise of GLP-1 medications like semaglutide (Wegovy, Ozempic) and tirzepatide (Mounjaro, Zepbound) has revolutionized weight loss treatment. However, with dozens of telehealth providers offering these medications, patients face a confusing marketplace with:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>Hidden fees and unclear pricing structures</li>
      <li>Varying levels of medical oversight and safety protocols</li>
      <li>Differences between brand-name and compounded medications</li>
      <li>Inconsistent customer support and refund policies</li>
      <li>Marketing claims that are difficult to verify</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>We created CompareWeightMeds to cut through the noise and provide objective, data-driven comparisons that put patient safety and transparency first.</p>
    
    <h2>Our Values</h2>
    
    <div class="values-grid">
      <div class="value-card">
        <div class="value-icon">üîç</div>
        <h4>Transparency</h4>
        <p>We clearly disclose our affiliate relationships and never let them influence our reviews or scores.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="value-card">
        <div class="value-icon">üè•</div>
        <h4>Safety First</h4>
        <p>We prioritize providers with proper medical oversight, licensed healthcare providers, and safe prescribing practices.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="value-card">
        <div class="value-icon">üìä</div>
        <h4>Data-Driven</h4>
        <p>Our proprietary TeleHealth Score (0-100) evaluates providers on 6 objective criteria, not marketing hype.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="value-card">
        <div class="value-icon">ü§ù</div>
        <h4>Patient-Focused</h4>
        <p>Every review and comparison is written from the patient perspective, addressing real concerns and questions.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>How We Review Providers</h2>
    <p>Our review process is rigorous and systematic. For each GLP-1 telehealth provider, we:</p>
    
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Research extensively:</strong> We analyze provider websites, pricing structures, medication offerings, and customer reviews from verified sources.</li>
      <li><strong>Verify credentials:</strong> We confirm that providers use licensed healthcare professionals and accredited pharmacies.</li>
      <li><strong>Compare pricing:</strong> We calculate total costs including consultation fees, membership fees, medication costs, and hidden charges.</li>
      <li><strong>Evaluate safety:</strong> We assess medical screening processes, prescription oversight, and patient support systems.</li>
      <li><strong>Score objectively:</strong> We apply our TeleHealth Score methodology to rate providers on 6 weighted factors.</li>
      <li><strong>Update regularly:</strong> We revisit reviews monthly to ensure pricing and information remain current.</li>
    </ol>
    
    <p>Learn more about our scoring methodology on our <a href="/methodology/">Methodology page</a>.</p>
    
    <h2>Our Team</h2>
    <p>CompareWeightMeds is maintained by a team of healthcare researchers, medical writers, and patient advocates with expertise in telehealth, weight management, and pharmaceutical safety. All content is reviewed for medical accuracy and updated regularly to reflect the latest information.</p>
    
    <h2>How We Make Money</h2>
    <p>We believe in full transparency about how we sustain this free resource:</p>
    
    <h3>Affiliate Commissions</h3>
    <p>When you click on a provider link and sign up for their service, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. These affiliate relationships help us maintain this comparison platform at no charge to users.</p>
    
    <h3>Editorial Independence</h3>
    <p>Importantly, our affiliate relationships do <strong>not</strong> influence our reviews, scores, or rankings. Providers cannot pay for better scores or preferential placement. Our TeleHealth Score methodology is applied consistently to all providers based on objective criteria.</p>
    
    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>Have questions, feedback, or concerns? We'd love to hear from you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> hello@compareweightmeds.com</li>
      <li><strong>Provider updates:</strong> If you represent a provider and have pricing or service updates, please contact us.</li>
      <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> Help us improve by sharing your experience with the providers we review.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>
    <p>CompareWeightMeds is an informational resource and comparison platform. We are not a medical provider and do not prescribe medications or provide medical advice. All information on this site is for educational purposes only. Always consult with a licensed healthcare professional before starting any weight loss medication or treatment program.</p>
    
    <p>GLP-1 medications like semaglutide and tirzepatide require a prescription and should only be used under medical supervision. Individual results may vary.</p>
    
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 48px; color: var(--text-sec);">
      Last Updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
